<p style= "text-align:justify" ><span style= "font-size: 14px" >Zelenogradsk, located at the very base <a href="https://koenigs.ru/post/3" > Curonian spit</a>, on the gentle slopes of dunes covered with pine and deciduous forests, earned the title of a popular resort at the beginning of the century before last. And today it does not part with its glory, luring tourists with a comfortable holiday on the sea coast, wide recreational opportunities. Zelenogradsk has the status of a climatic resort, where healing mud from peat bogs and mineral waters are also used for Spa treatment.</span></p>

<p><a href="https://static.koenigs.ru/images/blog/2/id2-001.jpg" target="_blank"><img alt="" class="img-responsive" src="https://static.koenigs.ru/images/blog/2/id2-001.jpg" style="height:300px; width:200px" /></a><a href="https://static.koenigs.ru/images/blog/2/id2-009.jpg" target="_blank"><img alt="" class="img-responsive" src="https://static.koenigs.ru/images/blog/2/id2-009.jpg" style="height:300px; margin-left:10px; margin-right:10px; width:325px" /></a></p>

<p style="text-align:justify"><span style="font-size:14px">Narrow clean streets paved with paving stones, neat houses covered with red tiles, well-groomed squares and parks give Zelenogradsk the features of an old German town, Recalling the times when It was a fashionable Prussian resort. But the promenade that stretches along the city's beaches looks quite modern. A wide embankment with restaurants, attractions, and a pier that goes out to sea is the most popular place for citizens and tourists in Zelenogradsk.</span></p>

<p style="text-align:justify"><span style="font-size:14px">More than two dozen hotels accept guests in the city, there are guest houses, as well as sanatoriums, boarding houses, where whole families often come to improve their health. On the streets there are many nice cafes with a varied menu, where fish dishes often occupy the main positions.</span></p>

<p style= "text-align:justify" > <span style="font-size:14px">Local guides offer walking tours of the city, this service is worth using, because many old buildings have an interesting history. When vacationing in Zelenogradsk, tourists always take the opportunity to go on a trip on <a href="https://koenigs.ru/post/3" target= "_blank" >Curonian spit</a>, where the national Park is located, famous for its unique natural attractions.</span></p>

<p style="text-align:justify"><span style="font-size:14px"><a href="https://static.koenigs.ru/images/blog/2/id2-010.jpg" target="_blank"><img alt="" class="img-responsive" src="https://static.koenigs.ru/images/blog/2/id2-010.jpg" style="height:300px; width:376px" /></a><a href="https://static.koenigs.ru/images/blog/2/id2-013.jpg" target="_blank"><img alt="" class="img-responsive" src="https://static.koenigs.ru/images/blog/2/id2-013.jpg" style="height:300px; margin-left:10px; margin-right:10px; width:425px" /></a></span></p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<h2 style= "text-align:justify" >Attractions in Zelenogradsk</h2>

<p style= "text-align:justify" > <span style= "font-size: 14px" >Resort life in Zelenogradsk runs smoothly in the Central and Eastern parts of the city. The Western district, built up in the Soviet era with similar houses, is not of interest to tourists. The exceptions are the railway station building, built at the end of the XIX century and recently restored, and the old Park with a pond. The reservoir is known as Tortilin pond &ndash; scenes with the wise turtle were shot here for the movie &laquo; the adventures of Pinocchio &raquo;. The Park has slides for children, volleyball courts, and a pond equipped with places for fishing.</span></p>

<p style="text-align:justify"><a href="https://static.koenigs.ru/images/blog/2/id2-006.jpg" target="_blank"><img alt="" class="img-responsive" src="https://static.koenigs.ru/images/blog/2/id2-006.jpg" style="height:300px; width:450px" /></a><a href="https://static.koenigs.ru/images/blog/2/id2-016.jpg" target="_blank"><img alt="" class="img-responsive" src="https://static.koenigs.ru/images/blog/2/id2-016.jpg" style="height:300px; margin-left:10px; margin-right:10px; width:348px" /></a></p>

<p style= "text-align:justify" ><span style= "font-size: 14px" >Famous landmark of the promenade &ndash; pump room &laquo; Queen Louise &raquo;. It was installed here in 2006 by one of the local patrons. The pump room is named after the Prussian Queen, who stayed in the city during her dramatic journey to <a href="https://koenigs.ru/post/3" > Curonian spit</a> from Konigsberg to Memel (Klaipeda), where she fled to escape the invasion of Napoleon's troops. A beautiful brick gazebo is built near a spring with mineral water coming from a depth of 240 m.</span></p>

<p style= "text-align:justify" ><span style= "font-size: 14px" >a small square near the promenade is also named after Queen Louise. A bust of the Queen is placed in this quiet and secluded place, and a long-lived elm tree grows in the center. Not far from the square, above the greenery of trees and tiled roofs of ancient buildings, the slender tower of the Orthodox Transfiguration Cathedral, a former Lutheran Church built in 1898 in honor of Saint Adalbert, rises into the sky.</span></p>

<p style="text-align:justify"><a href="https://static.koenigs.ru/images/blog/2/id2-008.jpg" target="_blank"><img alt="" class="img-responsive" src="https://static.koenigs.ru/images/blog/2/id2-008.jpg" style="height:300px; width:399px" /></a><a href="https://static.koenigs.ru/images/blog/2/id2-017.jpg" target="_blank"><img alt="" class="img-responsive" src="https://static.koenigs.ru/images/blog/2/id2-017.jpg" style="height:300px; margin-left:10px; margin-right:10px; width:400px" /></a></p>

<p style= "text-align:justify" > <span style= "font-size: 14px" >it is also Interesting to see the Church of St. Andrew, consecrated in 1998. This is the first Orthodox Church in Zelenogradsk. Previously, the red brick building with green spires was a Catholic chapel.</span></p>

<p style="text-align:justify"><span style="font-size:14px">Another ancient landmark of Zelenogradsk is the water tower. This forty-meter building, which is a symbol of the city, can be seen from all its corners. The top of the tower, from a distance resembling a hovering flying saucer, is equipped with an observation deck.</span></p>

<p style="text-align:justify"><span style="font-size:14px">The tower houses the lovely cat Museum &laquo; Murarium &raquo;. In his art collection, fluffy Pets are presented in the form of toys, figurines, jewelry, there are knitted, sewn, drawn cats.</span></p>

<p style="text-align:justify"><a href="https://static.koenigs.ru/images/blog/2/id2-007.jpg" target="_blank"><img alt="" class="img-responsive" src="https://static.koenigs.ru/images/blog/2/id2-007.jpg" style="height:300px; width:200px" /></a> <a href="https://static.koenigs.ru/images/blog/2/id2-005.jpg" target="_blank"> <img alt="" class="img-responsive" src="https://static.koenigs.ru/images/blog/2/id2-005.jpg" style="height:300px; margin-left:10px; margin-right:10px; width:428px" /></a></p>

<p style="text-align:justify"><span style="font-size:14px">Next to the Murarium is the Museum of skulls and skeletons. The Museum is divided into educational and interactive zones, where specific medical information is presented in an entertaining, humorous form. Bright and fun attraction &laquo; Ribbon maze &raquo; some consider creepy, others go through the maze again and again, if the first time you did not find a way out of it.</span></p>

<p style="text-align:justify"><span style="font-size:14px">A very different atmosphere prevails in the "House of Angels". This Museum has a unique collection of figurines, figurines, dolls of angels and angel-like creatures. Among the exhibits are bright author's works.</span></p>

<p style= "text-align:justify" > <span style= "font-size: 14px" >the Zelenograd Museum of local lore is the largest in this resort. The Museum is located in a mansion built at the beginning of the last century.</span></p>

<p style= "text-align:justify" ><span style= "font-size: 14px">Heading East from the Museum along the streets of Zelenogradsk, you will find yourself in an area with pre-war buildings. The narrow streets of old Krantz, paved with cobblestones, will lead you past beautiful buildings built in the late XIX-early XX century. In some places, houses with half-timbered (frame) construction Dating back to an earlier period have been preserved.</span></p>

<h2 style= "text-align:justify" >Beaches</h2>

<p style="text-align:justify"><span style="font-size:14px">Equipped coast is a single beach location, over part of which stretches the promenade. The beach strip is almost entirely covered with fine and soft Golden sand. Changing booths, toilets (paid), kiosks with drinks and food are located on the embankment. In summer, lifeguards are on duty on the beaches. The entrance to the sea here is convenient, very gentle, and to fully swim, you need to walk almost to the end of the breakwaters.</span></p>

<p style="text-align:justify"><span style="font-size:14px">Concerts and entertainment events are held at the wind rose square. Next to the square is a play area for children and a Bicycle rental service. Closer to the city Park, a wide boardwalk merges with a narrow wooden deck, but the coastal line here becomes wider. The beaches continue behind the equipped embankment. They are equipped with beach volleyball courts and water sports equipment rental facilities.</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify"><a href="https://static.koenigs.ru/images/blog/2/id2-012.jpg" target="_blank"><img alt="" class="img-responsive" src="https://static.koenigs.ru/images/blog/2/id2-012.jpg" style="height:300px; width:450px" /></a><a href="https://static.koenigs.ru/images/blog/2/id2-011.jpg" target="_blank"><img alt="" class="img-responsive" src="https://static.koenigs.ru/images/blog/2/id2-011.jpg" style="height:300px; margin-left:10px; margin-right:10px; width:249px" /></a></p>

<p style="text-align:justify"><span style="font-size:14px">The boardwalk, which stretches along the wide and spacious Western beaches, also offers recreational areas, cafes, sports and children's playgrounds. Stairs lead from the embankment to the sea. Closer to the outskirts of the city, the beach strip narrows, and there is almost no tourist infrastructure. Outside the city, Zelenogradsky beach meets the coastal strip of the village of Malinovka.</span></p>

<p style="text-align:justify"><span style="font-size:14px">Among the water sports on the beaches of Zelenogradsk is a popular surfing and SAP-surfing.</span></p>

<p style="text-align:justify"><span style="font-size:14px"><a href="https://static.koenigs.ru/images/blog/2/id2-002.jpg" target="_blank"><img alt="" class="img-responsive" src="https://static.koenigs.ru/images/blog/2/id2-002.jpg" style="height:267px; width:400px" /></a></span><span style="font-size:14px"><a href="https://static.koenigs.ru/images/blog/2/id2-005.jpg" target="_blank"><img alt="" class="img-responsive" src="https://static.koenigs.ru/images/blog/2/id2-003.jpg" style="height:267px; margin-left:10px; margin-right:10px; width:400px" /></a></span></p>

<h2 style="text-align:justify">Getting there</h2>

<p style= "text-align:justify"><span style= "font-size:14px">Tourists get to the coastal Zelenogradsk via Kaliningrad. </span></p>

<p style="text-align:justify"><span style="font-size:14px">The most convenient way to get to Zelenogradsk from Khrabrovo airport (Kaliningrad) is by minibus. Transport follows the Khrabrovo route &ndash; <a href="https://koenigs.ru/post/4">Svetlogorsk</a>, making stops in Pionerskoye and Zelenogradsk. The distance between the airport and Zelenogradsk is 25 km, the travel time is 40 minutes.</span></p>

<p style= "text-align:justify" ><span style= "font-size: 14px" >you can Get to Zelenogradsk from the airport by taxi or by rented car. You can rent a transport on our website in the section <a href="http://koenigs.ru/cars" > Auto</a>.</span></p>

